author: rhuijben
msg: In the merge code: fold notify_merge_begin() into its only caller, and
rename that caller to notify_merge_begin(). And then call this function
also for skips and tree conflicts.
Without this you could have skip, tree conflict followed by an header,
Somehow this patch makes some merge tests more vulnerable to ordering
(merge_cmd_baton_t): Add boolean. Remove nrb inner struct and some vars.
record_tree_conflict): Call notify_merge_begin. Remove const from baton.
(notify_merge_completed): Don't update variables to their +- defaults.
(notify_merge_begin): ... this. Use a boolean instead of a counter. Simplify
(do_mergeinfo_aware_dir_merge): Update baton usage. Reset header state.
(merge_target_selection): Update expected result of tree conflicted only merges.
